##Liu Liang's team's first autopsy report on a new crown: it's different from SARS

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By He Liping and Zhang Ruoting, _ the _ paper _

The autopsy of the first and second cases of NCP was completed on February 16 at Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital, with the permission of legal policy and the consent of the patient's family. From February 16 to February 24, the Huazhong University of Science and Technology, led by Liu Liang and professor Wang Guoping, department of Pathology, Tongji Hospital, completed nine autopsies. Pathology expert academician Bian Xiuwu and the team of Shanghai Ruijin Hospital have also completed the autopsy of 2 cases of NCP.

From thepaper.cn: Zhu Wenbo, Editor: Lin Rong, Video Source: person in Charge Editor: Zhou Qi

A few days ago, liu Liang's team published one of these anatomical observations in the February 2020 issue of the Journal of Forensic Medicine, Vol. 36, No. 1, in the Journal of COVID-19, the paper was accepted on February 24. In addition to Liu Liang, the corresponding authors include Zhou Yiwu and Ren Liang of the Department of Forensic Medicine at Tongji Medical College. In addition to the Tongji Medical College, the authors include staff members from the Chongxin forensic science center in Hubei Province and the Shanghai Public Security College.

"report" is a case of systematic autopsy results of naked eye observation. The team points out that the deceased had significant lung damage. To the naked eye, the lungs were patchy, with gray-white Lesions and dark-red hemorrhages, it is suggested that npv mainly causes deep airway and Alveolar injury, which is characterized by inflammatory response.

On the 13th day after admission for multiple cerebral infarction, the patient tested positive for COVID-19 nucleic acid and was confirmed to have COVID-19 infection. On the 20th day after admission, the CT scan showed that the lung was scattered in the patchy infection focus, and the original tracheal secretion had disappeared when the "viral pneumonia" was considered. Died 28 days after admission. The clinical cause of death was diagnosed as COVID-19 pneumonia and respiratory failure.

It should be noted that the histopathologic changes obtained from the cadavers of the deceased with the new pneumonia suggest that the pathological features of the new pneumonia are very similar to those of SARS and Mers patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
However, according to the report, from the gross anatomy of this case, the pulmonary fibrosis and consolidation were not as severe as those caused by SARS, and the exudative reaction was more obvious than that caused by SARS, which may be related to the fact that the patient died only 15 days after diagnosis, the shorter course of the disease is relevant, pending more systematic autopsy data and histopathology verification.

On February 27, at a news briefing for the Special News Session on Epidemic Prevention and control in Guangzhou, Zhong Nanshan, head of the High Level Expert Group of the National Health and Health Commission and Director of the respiratory disease, also mentioned the pathological characteristics of NCP, unlike SARS, NCP has a distinctive feature: A large amount of mucus in the small airways, which is very sticky and obstructs the passage of the airways, resulting in secondary infection and further aggravation. The removal of Mucus from the Small Airways has been an important subject of study from both pathologic findings.

"report" showed that the amount of pleural effusion of the deceased was not much, Pale yellow clear fluid, did not see a large number of pleural fluid production, suggesting that pleural lesions are not mainly serous inflammation.

In addition, the anatomy of the pericardial cavity medium light yellow clear fluid, epicardial mild edema, myocardial section was gray-red fish-like. Because of the clinical data of patients with coronary heart disease and Angina Pectoris, whether there is myocardial and epicardium damage related to virus infection needs to be further studied.

The injury of digestive system in this case is not obvious to the naked eye. In particular, the researchers found that the small intestine was segmental dilatation and stricture (similar to beading) , which required more postmortem examination, either individually or in general. The gross appearance of the spleen is not abnormal, and the presence or absence of lesions should be studied by histopathology. The appearance of the kidney was granular constriction, which was related to the underlying disease.

Regarding the nervous system, the naked eye sees the brain dropsy, the cerebrum cortex slight atrophy. Combined with clinical data, the patient was old, had multiple cerebral infarction and cerebrovascular disease sequelae, no specific manifestation of infection was found in the naked eye of the brain, and whether the virus invaded the central nervous system should be verified by histopathology.

Since December 2019, COVID-19 pneumonia has caused more than 70,000 confirmed infections and more than 2,000 deaths in China, Liu Liang's team wrote in the report. As of February 24,2020, the national mortality rate of patients with NCP was 3.17% . Among the 99 cases of COVID-19 previously reported in Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, 11 cases died and the mortality rate was 11% .

Due to the lack of systematic autopsy to provide a complete set of pathological data, researchers on the pathogenesis of disease, organ damage and other effects can not be accurately determined. Liu Liang's team believes that the autopsy report provides an intuitive picture of the disease, or will provide evidence for clinical treatment options.

Autopsy is considered to be an important link in epidemic prevention and control, which is the gold standard to find out the cause of death, analyze the pathogenesis and trace the source of disease. It is worth mentioning that, prior to the autopsy, there were 2 reports of pathological examination related to the death of NCP, but no autopsy was performed.

One is from a team led by Professor Wang Fusheng, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and Director of the National Center for Clinical Research on infectious diseases, the findings, published Feb. 18 in The Lancet Respiratory Medicine, suggest that The pathology of Acute Respiratory distress syndrome is associated with pneumonia. Another article was published on Preprint on Feb. 16 by Xiao Shuyuan, director of Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital, the results of pathological examination of lung tissue in a patient with lung tumor complicated with new pneumonia after pneumonectomy were reported.
